description:
Add CSS styles for GraphRAG dashboard components to arcana.css.

**New CSS Classes:**

```css
/* Sub-tab navigation within Graph page */
.arcana-graph-subtabs { }

/* Entity/Relationship/Community tables */
.arcana-graph-table { }

/* Type badges (person, organization, technology, concept) */
.arcana-entity-type-badge { }
.arcana-entity-type-badge.person { }
.arcana-entity-type-badge.organization { }
.arcana-entity-type-badge.technology { }
.arcana-entity-type-badge.concept { }

/* Relationship strength visual (10-dot meter) */
.arcana-strength-meter { }
.arcana-strength-dot { }
.arcana-strength-dot.filled { }

/* Detail panels */
.arcana-entity-detail { }
.arcana-relationship-detail { }
.arcana-community-detail { }

/* Community summary box */
.arcana-community-summary { }

/* Graph context section in Ask results */
.arcana-graph-context { }
.arcana-matched-entities { }
.arcana-matched-relationships { }

/* Chunk attribution (via: entity1, entity2) */
.arcana-chunk-attribution { }

/* Collection graph-enabled indicators */
.arcana-graph-enabled { }
.arcana-graph-disabled { }

/* Status indicators for communities */
.arcana-status-ready { }    /* ✓ */
.arcana-status-pending { }  /* ⟳ */
.arcana-status-empty { }    /* ○ */
```

**Design Notes:**
- Match existing dashboard aesthetic
- Entity type badges use distinct but subtle colors
- Strength meter uses primary color for filled dots, muted for empty
- Detail panels use same card style as existing search results
